This has been fixed in CVS HEAD:

   [ 1219262 ] &#39;treat seed redirects as new seeds&#39; not working
   http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1219262&group_id=73833&atid=539099

This feature has always been a bit flaky and dangerous, sometimes
bringing in far more than we intended on our crawls; it may be
replaced with a more manual approach later. For example: you get
a report of seeds that generated out-of-scope redirects, and then
have to confirm those (or all) that you want fed back in as new
seeds.

- Gordon @ IA

